"From today, one wonders: How could I just so wrong?"
He was huge.
In 2007, for the first time appears to be that if something went wrong at UBS.
In the middle of the year, Chief Executive Peter Wuffli surprising back, until such time as high intellectual and equally ingenious bankers.
A few months later, you guessed what, why he had gone.
The investment banking division had with sub-prime securities verzockt and had to write off billions.
