But that was only the first blow.
In April 2008, there was worse.
The bank had to announce new billion losses, Board President Marcel Ospel, 2006, the second-best paid board of Switzerland, resigned.
In October 2008, following the disaster, the UBS was given its bad investments in the financial crisis before the collapse and had to be rescued by the state.
The National Bank bought the UBS for tens of billions of problematic securities, the Swiss Confederation, six billion francs for a mandatory convertible bond, which the bank they Miteigentümerin.
