The headquarters of UBS in Zurich fits the stereotype of sterling Swiss private bank - it is just a bit bigger.
The situation is classic.
The Bank has its headquarters in Zurich railway station, the main train station from the Zürichsee leads directly by the snow covered summits of the Swiss mountains frames.
The buildings here are magnificent, the shop rents are among the highest in Europe.
Juweliere as Tiffany's can be found here between Swiss tradition shops like Confiserie Sprüngli.
Stay here for centuries, the Swiss banks, the National Bank of the palace of Credit Suisse to elite private banks such as Julius Bear.
The reception hall of UBS, one enters through a heavy revolving door.
Inside, the walls are thick marble disguised, leather chair, in addition to the bank's logo is a great sign for "safe".
The UBS knows what the customer is looking here: Security.
This idea of the Swiss bank have both Swiss big banks, UBS and Credit Suisse, but eventually supplanted - or, as the head of a small Swiss private bank.
His name, he would prefer not to read in the newspaper, after all, he, like all Swiss bankers, even with the two big banks.
The UBS is far too big, he finds - particularly in investment banking, where the Anglo-Saxons had spread.
The Swiss have nothing more to say there.
"And if they do, they have long since the habits of the Anglo-Saxons."
Indeed, it was the Anglo-Saxon investment banking, UBS modified, their only received high profits and then the debacle: No European financial institution in the subprime jungle lost as much money as the Swiss large bank.
On 15 October 2008, the disaster.
"On that Wednesday, the coalition government of the small country of seven million, the largest rescue operation in the history of their nation," writes the author Lukas Hässig in his book "The UBS-crash."
Up to 68 billion francs, or roughly 45 billion euros allocated the politicians, from bankruptcy in order to save the big banks.
How could this happen?
Talk with Swiss bankers, so they see the problem, especially in the size of the UBS.
In June 1998, two of the three Swiss big banks to a huge corporation.
There was a bank that the merger was too big for the small Swiss - and increasingly grew.
It helped that the two different precursor-banks UBS supplemented: A rich, but verschlafene bank with a focus on asset management in Zurich and a poorer, but even more internationalized.
Suddenly, the internationalised investment bankers favourable to a lot of money with which they have a huge wheel.
Two names are on the rise of the UBS: Peter Wuffli, from 2001 to 2007, group chief executive of UBS, Marcel Ospel, chairman of the Board of Directors.
"I always thought that Wuffli and Ospel are a dream team," says banks researchers Hans Geiger.
"Wuffli, higher intellectuals, modest, a lot of models and statistics, and Ospel, the hard man, who is from the bank lesson to top up."
But Ospel was finally left to Wuffli.
And in the end Wuffli have probably made a crucial mistake, "he thought his models are the reality," says Geiger.
"This is a tragic case."
Tragic, perhaps.
It is clear: Excess came before the fall.
Staff at the UBS will remember clearly to the leaders' meetings in which company chief Wuffli was always the same slogan: Goldman Sachs Dethrone.
The US bank was the most powerful investment bank on the planet.
They led the league with "in the rankings, the success of the banks that time documented.
Then, wanted to UBS, according to the top.
A few steps, she has managed to do so.
In foreign exchange business and the stock was trading at the top with them.
Corporate advisers who have been charged, but stressed a weakness: International interest in the business, in which bankers language "surprise fixed Income," there is a huge gap with the largest banks.
The UBS have gaps in mortgage products.
To close the gap left UBS in an adventure that nearly cost them their existence.
Hungry for growth, both the Bank itself invested and above their established hedge funds in American sub-prime assets.
It became a huge machine, the securities on US mortgage loans packaged and far-reaching, but also risks maintained.
Also, as other banks have sought out.
"Even in the summer of 2007, when the US housing market was on fire, the UBS bought there," says banking expert Geiger.
So great the euphoria, so deep.
A manager had to go after the other and clean up the experiments tested more difficult than thought.
Items in the UBS became the weapon and are still shaky.
Anyone who now leads the major bank, has an almost impossible job.
He needs to find a strategy for a bank, which lost all obvious business models.
Banks researchers Geiger already has an idea: Stop the investment banking, focus on asset management, return to the Swiss roots.
So far, the Bank may not (yet).
But that investment banking is expected to shrink sharply, so much is already clear.
On Thursday, the new bank chief Sergio Ermotti the world its future strategy.
The 51-year-old Italo-Swiss was actually intended only as a temporary solution, as the bank is surprising Grübel separated by predecessor.
Meanwhile, he has won: He is in the business of UBS, told the Zurich bank on Tuesday.
Ermotti wants the investment bank to roll back the in the mid-1990s.
He cut 3,500 jobs.
But it will not be enough.
The UBS needs a vision.
Who is it?
What do you make money?
These are the questions that Axel Weber sure now.
So far only publicly he says that he and his wife, once a home in Zurich.
Next year.
