Lies ruin careers and shaking countries.
The New York Congressman Anthony Weidner and Internetexhibitionist made a fool of himself when he renunciations in circulation, the very quickly refuted by incontrovertible evidence.
The former presidential candidate John Edwards is accused in the campaign finance violations in connection with the cover-up of an extramarital affair.
And then, of course, no one forgets that it has experienced the media circus that President Bill Clinton as he has during his second term in the Oval Office about his sexual relationship with Monica Lewinsky lied.
Stories of cheating in school and college examinations are widespread.
There have been incidents in which teachers to their students took the exam answers so that they themselves in their performance on tests any good.
Mentors who teach the opposite should send a message that lying and cheating OK.
We have seen how much deception?
As studies show that every day we lie between 10 and 200 times.
Many of these lies, but as lies.
Another study shows that strangers each other three times during the first 10 minutes of a meeting lie.
Lies to recognize lies uncover "to learn is that for every human being is important, both for personal and professional reasons.
Far from a parlor game such as host Aden, where the goal is to "property you!" To expose the deception is a serious know area that is based on scientific data over the past six decades of prestigious universities, the wide-ranging research projects, particularly in the fields of psychology and physiology.
A result of the research is that most of the old myths about the lies were revealed.
Look into the eyes of a lie.
They stottern, stammeln zappeln suffused with, and not always.
But we should not conclude from this that these liars are difficult to detect and expose.
A geübter Lügenenttarner can penetrate the truth, something about the structure of the claim that the subtle facial expressions, question and timing.
I have spent several years, the science of comprehensive and ever-growing area of exposing. And it is clear that the ability to expose the deception is a modern, which is easy to learn and we find in our complex world helps, especially if the suspensions or the questioning of persons or negotiations or management to their own professional responsibilities.
Good liar are very good people to assess their interests and to control their own emotions, and they sense intuitively, how they are perceived by others.
Thanks to the research, we know that people are more likely to lie than extrovertierte introvertierte people that men are more likely to "self-oriented" lies are than women whose lies more "to other guide" - typically, they want to protect the feelings of others - that married people reneging on its partners less often than unmarried people (but the lies they tell are mostly "fat lies").
We also know that if a person has been revealed as a culprit, others feel less guilty, this person angelogen.
As you can see whether someone is lying?
First of all, by the normal behaviour of this person.
It is called "Baselining", the starting position.
It is a point of reference for later assessment of changes.
You see the attitude, the laughter, the Stimmqualität their attempt person.
They should know better, usually when someone constantly with the foot trippelt, so that they do not unfairly when he during a meeting with the foot trippelt.
Then you look at accumulations striking verbal and nonverbaler behaviour.
Consider these accumulations as a warning bell ringing, not as evidence of exposing.
People who grind to a halt, perhaps, if they try to remember their history, perhaps, their feet towards the door or in the direction they are starting to change their position in a significant way, or show a "relaxation after the cessation conversation," this deep, entspannende breathed out by others and the change in attitude that if all the hard questions are over.
Often mistakenly Fragende signal that a recruitment conversation is over, just after this relaxation after the cessation conversation.
You also look at the language of your attempt person.
The slip of Scott Peterson is famous when he used the past tense when he claimed that his wife was killed on live and a national search for her.
Deceptive individuals can also use a distanzierende language: "I did not have sexual relations with that woman... Miss Lewinsky" or if a vexed issue in its entirety.
The most frequent verbal signs are subtle.
Some people use "qualifying language" if it is a vexed question: "Now... to tell you the truth... as far as I know... in good faith."
This is the answer, rather than objectively true reference, which often set the alarm bells ringing.
There is no magic means to expose of lies, but you can learn skills, thanks to which a exposing is possible.
Thanks to these skills, anyone can be a victim of fraudsters, both in private and professional life.
