A statement from the presidential palace announced that the Sunday appointed Monti on Wednesday with the president, Giorgio Napolitano, would make the government.
It is expected that a majority will present special cabinet of technocrats, although it is not yet clear when the new prime minister will assume office.
Monti said he would give the president the outcome of the talks with the political parties to form a government.
