After recent revival at the end of last week, when it became known that Berlusconi would resign, as a result of the uncertainty about the success of the new Prime Minister, the cost to the Italian government bonds back critical borders.
A bailout of Italy, with a public debt of 1.8 trillion euros, would be too much for the current EU rescue package.
