Park or mountain?
The architects, apart from the disputes over the fees with the tender.
The urban tender on 16 gates opened the debate about the importance of Collserola again in Barcelona.
In the mid-1980s, at the height of the now missing Spanish Metropolitana de Barcelona (CMB), published this administration on the promotion of their Schmähschrift Collserola.
The brochure described the mountain as a huge park in Barcelona city.
He was even in figures with the Central Park in New York in comparison.
With the demise of the CMB in 1987, the park in the eyes of many back to the ceiling of Barcelona, the capital of Catalonia is one of the few who are not in north-south direction, but upwards (mountains) and below (Sea).
The classification Collserolas plays as a natural park with this idea.
Now no longer served as an example of Central Park, but Yellow Stone with wild boar in the role of Yogibärs.
So far, it was when the city in September a giant tender, consisting of 16 competitions, for further access gates after Collserola purported.
Undoubtedly, a gateway to the concept of a park.
Either that, or someone has, gates to the countryside.
The question is: Collserola, parking or mountain?
The tender is not only from the organizational point of view, but also in terms of a reflection on the city the topic of discussion in the mouths of all architects from Barcelona.
It is almost a rekurrentes issue that two members of the old eingesessenen caste in the lift,.
