After three quarters of fall, the details of the gross domestic product between July and September, finally to close this chapter: GDP grew by 1.5% compared to the previous quarter and 6% for the year hochgerechnete rate.
The measured value in the second quarter of the business year starting in Japan in March 2012 - also means the fastest growth since the period from January to March 2010.
The recovery is partly by the machinery sales for the rebuilding of the earthquake and subsequent tsunami-ravaged areas.
Indeed, the company increased its investment by 1.1% compared to the drop of 0.9% for investments, which were recorded from January to March, the first decline after six months of relentless increases.
Yet the real change based on the Japanese economy not only from Keynesian Anstößen who take advantage of the crisis to build infrastructure or build new ones.
Japan is particularly woke up, thanks to the development of domestic consumption, which currently accounts for 60% of Japan's GDP.
This variable rose by 1%, driven by the increased spending on cars, travel and leisure activities.
