Registration of "Golden budget rule in the constitution
In Austria, the government in power groβen socialist/Christian Democrat coalition has decided on Tuesday, a "golden budget rule in the constitution, in order to reduce public deficits and a possible degradation by rating agencies in the top-rated Austria (AAA).
It was the Social Democratic Chancellor Werner, Mr Faymann very personally, this decision ends of the Council of Ministers, although the public Austrian national debt in 74.6%, i.e. far above the benchmark set by the Maastricht Treaty of 60%, but significantly below the level of debt of countries such as Italy, Greece or Spain.
"If the solvency of Austria in one fell swoop down from AAA to AA +, so we should each year to pay an additional three billion euro interest rates," said Michael Spindelegger, Vice-Chancellor and Christian Democrat Auβenminister.
Austria is also a requirement of the Brussels summit of eurozone Member States on 26 October, the Heads of State and Government had at the time, including the reduction of public deficits by the end of 2012, and a return to the public accounts equal weight in the Constitution or by adopting a similar law.
In this respect from the Austrian government's Maβnahme resembles the "German model", because Germany was the first European country that such a "rule" in the Constitution.
By the year 2017 if the structural budget deficit every year by 0.75% of gross domestic product (GDP), from 2017, the structural budget deficit of the state of the 0.35% of GDP, while the regional states as well as the communities are balanced budgets.
The aim is to the horizon of 2020/21, household debt under the set by the Maastricht treaty 60% criterion.
